abstract: One of President Donald Trump’s top reelection advisers told influential Republicans in swing state Wisconsin that the party has “traditionally” relied on voter suppression to compete in battleground states, according to an audio recording of a private event obtained by The Associated Press. The adviser said later that his remarks referred to frequent and false accusations that Republicans employ such tactics.
snippet: One of President Donald Trump’s top reelection advisers told influential Republicans in swing state Wisconsin that the party has “traditionally” relied on voter suppression to compete in battleground states, according to an audio recording of a pr...
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — One of President Donald Trump’s top reelection advisers told influential Republicans in swing state Wisconsin that the party has “traditionally” relied on voter suppression to compete in battleground states, according to an audio recording of a private event obtained by The Associated Press. The adviser said later that his remarks referred to frequent and false accusations that Republicans employ such tactics.
headline_main: Trump Adviser: Expect More Aggressive Poll Watching in 2020
headline_print_headline: Trump Adviser: Expect More Aggressive Poll Watching in 2020

abstract: Christianity Today’s call for President Trump’s removal gave voice to his evangelical critics. But they remain a minority in a political movement that Mr. Trump has reshaped in his own mold.

lead_paragraph: The publication is small, reaching just a fraction of the evangelical movement.

headline_main: Evangelical Leaders Close Ranks With Trump After Scathing Editorial
byline_original: By Elizabeth Dias and Jeremy W. Peters

abstract: Democrats have one, too, and impeached the president on it.
snippet: Democrats have one, too, and impeached the president on it.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s impeachment is the result of a conspiracy theory. Democrats and other supporters of the charges against Mr. Trump might be reluctant to accept that labeling. But a conspiracy theory is not necessarily crackpot or wrong: If the conspiracy is real, the theory may be correct.

abstract: A conservative law firm asked the Wisconsin Supreme Court on Friday to bypass a lower court and take the appeal of a ruling that ordered the purge of more than 200,000 voter registrations in the battleground state ahead of the 2020 election.
snippet: A conservative law firm asked the Wisconsin Supreme Court on Friday to bypass a lower court and take the appeal of a ruling that ordered the purge of more than 200,000 voter registrations in the battleground state ahead of the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — A conservative law firm asked the Wisconsin Supreme Court on Friday to bypass a lower court and take the appeal of a ruling that ordered the purge of more than 200,000 voter registrations in the battleground state ahead of the 2020 election.
headline_main: Wisconsin Supreme Court Asked to Take Over Voter Purge Case
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Supreme Court Asked to Take Over Voter Purge Case

abstract: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
snippet: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday, a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
headline_main: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future
headline_print_headline: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future

abstract: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
snippet: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Monica Crowley, the Treasury Department’s assistant secretary for public affairs, committed “localized instances of plagiarism” in her 2000 Ph.D. dissertation, Columbia University found in an investigation that ultimately concluded she did not commit research misconduct.

abstract: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper said on Friday that he remains hopeful the United States can restart diplomacy with North Korea, as the clock ticks down to North Korea's declared year-end deadline for new U.S. concessions in talks over its nuclear arsenal.
snippet: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper said on Friday that he remains hopeful the United States can restart diplomacy with North Korea, as the clock ticks down to North Korea's declared year-end deadline for new U.S. concessions in talks over its nucle...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper said on Friday that he remains hopeful the United States can restart diplomacy with North Korea, as the clock ticks down to North Korea's declared year-end deadline for new U.S. concessions in talks over its nuclear arsenal.
headline_main: Pentagon Chief Hopeful for Restarting Diplomacy With North Korea, but Stands Ready
